		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/07/23/today-in-small-business-amazons-unbreachable-moat/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Amazon&#8217;s &#8216;Unbreachable Moat&#8217;" data-description="A Miami diner that was a pioneer in race relations closes after six decades. After many strike-outs, an entrepreneur hits a $44 million home run. And how Comcast trains its customer service representatives.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>The Economy</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Sales of existing homes hit their <a href="//www.usatoday.com/story/money/business/2014/07/22/june-existing-home-sales/12973181/">fastest pace since October</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Casino operators are <a href="//www.psmag.com/navigation/business-economics/vegas-strip-blackjack-rule-change-sleight-hand-86193/">changing blackjack payouts</a> to give the house an even greater advantage &#8212; a sign that the economy in Las Vegas may be improving.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Customer Service</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ An internal <a href="//consumerist.com/2014/07/21/comcast-memo-rep-from-painful-retention-call-was-doing-what-we-trained-him-to-do/">Comcast memo</a> defends that now-famous customer service representative.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Facebook <a href="//www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2014/07/22/facebook-customer-satisfaction/12994539/">scores low</a> in a customer-satisfaction survey. <span id="more-87460"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Start-Up</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A marketing analytics start-up <a href="//techcrunch.com/2014/07/22/quantifind-funding/">led by former physicists</a> raises $12 million.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Health Care</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Ezra Klein writes that Tuesday&#8217;s appellate court ruling against the Affordable Care Act is &#8220;<a href="//www.vox.com/2014/7/22/5926339/no-the-halbig-case-isnt-going-to-destroy-obamacare">plainly ridiculous</a>&#8221; &#8212; and that the &#8220;Supreme Court simply isn&#8217;t going to rip insurance from tens of millions of people in order to teach Congress a lesson about grammar.&#8221;</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Around the Country</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A Miami diner that was a <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/23/us/jumbos-restaurant-closing-in-miami.html">pioneer in race relations</a> closes after six decades.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Almost <a href="//www.spearswms.com/news/revealed-cities-with-the-highest-percentage-of-millionaires-4323521#.U87b4vldW7r">5 percent of New Yorkers</a> are millionaires and here are the <a href="//time.com/money/3014512/richest-wealthiest-highest-income-counties-america-united-states/">10 richest counties</a> in America.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A man with a <a href="//www.nj.com/cumberland/index.ssf/2014/07/suspect_with_sock_full_of_money_scams_vineland_business_owner.html">sock full of money</a> is suspected of swindling a New Jersey business owner.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A Brooklyn bar owner is <a href="//gawker.com/brooklyn-bar-owner-sentenced-to-prison-after-scamming-1-1608874619">sentenced to prison</a> after swindling 100 wedding couples.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ In Virginia, a <a href="//www.dailyprogress.com/news/local/year-old-nelson-mill-still-grinding-away/article_1aa34e88-0ec2-11e4-91fe-001a4bcf6878.html">220-year-old mill</a> still produces stone-ground grits, flour and meal.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Virginiaâs governor <a href="//www.timesdispatch.com/business/small-business/mcauliffe-orders-more-state-contracts-assigned-to-small-businesses/article_82312802-118f-11e4-92e4-001a4bcf6878.html">signed an executive order</a> requiring state agencies to award more than 42 percent of contracts to small businesses.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Retailing</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Chipotleâs executives say they <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/chipotle-is-building-tiny-restaurants-2014-7?">are experimenting</a> with âreally small, scrappyâ restaurants.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ As its Prime membership becomes retailingâs most <a href="//qz.com/237933/amazon-is-building-the-retail-worlds-most-unbreachable-moat-and-its-called-prime/">âunbreachable moat,â</a> Amazon unveils a <a href="//www.engadget.com/2014/07/22/amazon-wallet/?n">new service</a> for managing payments.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ But for brick-and-mortar retailers, maybe there is a <a href="//www.inc.com/gene-marks/how-to-defeat-showrooming.html">way to beat</a> âshowrooming.â</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Employees</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Here is why the 9-to-5 workday is <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/wonkblog/wp/2014/07/22/science-were-more-likely-to-lie-and-cheat-when-were-tired/">practically an invitation</a> to ethical lapses.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ President Obama <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/23/us/obama-signs-new-job-training-law.html?">signs a new job-training law</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Apple is hit with a <a href="//valleywag.gawker.com/apple-is-now-facing-a-class-action-lawsuit-for-unpaid-w-1609218927">class-action lawsuit</a> over unpaid wages.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ There is evidence that <a href="//www.vox.com/2014/7/22/5926557/big-chains-pay-better-than-mom-and-pop-stores">big stores and big chains</a> pay employees more than small businesses do.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Ideas</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Two parents are hoping to sell safe and practical <a href="//www.newsguardian.co.uk/news/local/pair-hoping-for-cash-support-for-business-1-6742349">tableware for children</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ An eccentric taxidermist has <a href="//www.express.co.uk/news/weird/490313/Cruel-or-drop-DEAD-gorgeous-Taxidermist-designs-one-off-fascinators-using-animal-corpses">designed a collection</a> of macabre fashion accessories using animal corpses.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A law firm <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/twincities/blog/law/2014/07/fafinski-mark-johnson-adds-drone-practice.html">adds a drone practice</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Around the World</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A new <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/23/dining/made-in-house-prove-it.html">consumer protection law in France</a> is intended to inform restaurant patrons whether a dish is fait maison &#8212; made in the house &#8212; or prepared elsewhere.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">The Federal Aviation Administration <a href="//abcnews.go.com/Travel/faa-orders-us-air-carriers-suspend-flights-israel/story?id=24663989">halts all American flights</a> to Israel.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ EBay <a href="//www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/business/industries/retailing/article4154773.ece">announces plans</a> to extend credit to small businesses through its PayPal subsidiary.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Online</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ More than 500 URLs have been <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/most-expensive-domain-names-2014-7">sold for $1 million</a> or more.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The United States <a href="//gigaom.com/2014/07/22/report-the-u-s-joins-6-other-countries-in-achieving-100-wireless-data-penetration/">joins six other countries</a> in achieving 100 percent mobile or wireless data penetration, or both.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Entrepreneurship</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ After many strike-outs, an entrepreneur hits <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/235796">a $44 million</a> home run.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Social Media</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ LinkedIn <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/linkedin-acquiring-bizo-for-175-million-2014-7">acquires</a> a business-to-business advertising company.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Here are eight <a href="//www.thehubcomms.com/the-8-types-of-tweets-that-generate-engagement-on-twitter/article/362237/">types of tweets</a> that generate engagement.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The number of employers <a href="//www.bulldogreporter.com/dailydog/article/pr-biz-update/hiring-departments-social-carnage-number-of-employers-passing-on-appl#.">declining to hire applicants</a> because of social media posts continues to rise, according to a survey.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Opportunities</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Google <a href="//techcrunch.com/2014/07/22/google-opens-1m-contest-to-shrink-a-power-inverter/?ncid=rss">plans to give away</a> $1 million to a group that creates a smaller and cheaper power inverter.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A newly formed unit of Universal Music Group <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/235843">is scouring</a> YouTube channels to find the next big recording star.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Technology</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Apple reports a <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/23/technology/apple-reports-7-7-billion-profit-in-third-quarter.html?">$7.7 billion profit</a> on strong iPhone sales.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Verizonâs profit <a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/verizons-profit-improves-1406025632?m">improves sharply</a>, thanks to tablet sales.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A group of ex-Googlers are <a href="//www.wired.com/2014/07/cockroachdb/">building cloud software</a> that is almost impossible to take down.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><em>Gene Marks owns the <a href="//www.marksgroup.net">Marks Group</a>, a Bala Cynwyd, Pa., consulting firm that helps clients with customer relationship management. You can follow him on <a href="https://www.twitter.com/genemarks">Twitter</a>.</em></p>
